keyFacts: The document is an FBI FD-340 evidence receipt form, indicating formal handling of investigative materials.
It references an interview with Edward S., whose full name may be Edward Staley based on context from other documents.
The material includes original interview notes and photographs.
The form marks the material as Grand Jury Material, restricting dissemination under Federal Rule of Criminal Procedure 6(e).
The form also indicates the material contains Federal Taxpayer Information (FTI), suggesting financial aspects to the investigation.
